1
00:00:01,101 --> 00:00:12,346
♪

2
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:14,348
(heavy breathing)

3
00:00:14,348 --> 00:00:15,849
I'm burning up.

4
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,351
It's not even 8:00
in the morning.

5
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:19,186
Why does it have
to be so hot?

6
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:21,288
It's summer, yo.

7
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:22,422
Oh.

8
00:00:22,422 --> 00:00:23,857
Would you stop
wasting your breath

9
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:25,025
saying, "Yo," all the time?

10
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:26,627
You're just making it hotter.

11
00:00:26,627 --> 00:00:28,428
I'm not wasting
my breath, yo.

12
00:00:28,428 --> 00:00:30,364
I told you to
stop saying that!

13
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:31,765
I can say whatever I want,

14
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:34,101
and there's not a thing
you can do about it, yo.

15
00:00:34,101 --> 00:00:35,168
You think so?

16
00:00:35,168 --> 00:00:36,270
Yeah, yo.

17
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:37,905
Hey, how about
you two stop acting

18
00:00:37,905 --> 00:00:39,907
like a couple of babies?

19
00:00:39,907 --> 00:00:41,008
‐Take a hike!
‐Take a hike!

20
00:00:41,008 --> 00:00:42,409
What did you say?

21
00:00:42,409 --> 00:00:45,946
‐Oh, uh, hi, Kamui.
‐Oh, uh, hi, Kamui.

22
00:00:45,946 --> 00:00:47,447
Why aren't you
at Card Capital?

23
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:48,682
We're not leaving
for a while,

24
00:00:48,682 --> 00:00:50,584
so I thought I'd
come see you off.

25
00:00:50,584 --> 00:00:52,119
But, listen, you guys
are gonna have

26
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:54,755
a long train ride today,
so you better stop arguing.

27
00:00:54,755 --> 00:00:56,223
Besides, who could be upset

28
00:00:56,223 --> 00:00:57,958
with all this beautiful
weather we're having?

29
00:00:57,958 --> 00:00:59,192
Beautiful, huh?

30
00:00:59,192 --> 00:01:01,962
Kamui, aren't you
feeling the heat at all?

31
00:01:01,962 --> 00:01:04,531
Now that you mention it,
I am pretty toasty.

32
00:01:04,531 --> 00:01:07,034
But this scorching weather
is just what we needed.

33
00:01:07,034 --> 00:01:09,036
What do you mean?

34
00:01:09,036 --> 00:01:12,739
It's the blazing hot start
to the national tournament!

35
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:13,941
Oh, right.

36
00:01:13,941 --> 00:01:15,709
I still don't get it, yo.

37
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:17,644
If the other teams think
they're sweating now,

38
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:19,813
just wait till they
get a load of us.

39
00:01:21,014 --> 00:02:49,236
♪

40
00:02:54,474 --> 00:02:57,577
Oh, man, it's gonna
take hours to get there.

41
00:02:57,577 --> 00:02:59,680
It's got to be nice that you
don't have to come with us

42
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,815
on the smelly, old train, yo.

43
00:03:01,815 --> 00:03:03,784
Trust me, it's not
as good as it sounds.

44
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:06,086
You haven't seen
Shin's driving.

45
00:03:06,086 --> 00:03:08,989
(sneezing)

46
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:11,124
(sniffing)

47
00:03:11,124 --> 00:03:13,060
I can't believe all of
you guys are gonna try

48
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:15,495
to pile into that
tiny van for the trip.

49
00:03:15,495 --> 00:03:17,898
Don't forget about
their bags and Kai's ego.

50
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:19,700
It's gonna be a
tight squeeze, yo.

51
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,968
Ha, do me a favor,
and don't even mention

52
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:23,603
that jerk in front of me.

53
00:03:23,603 --> 00:03:25,372
Not a fan of Mr. Mean?

54
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:26,406
As if.

55
00:03:26,406 --> 00:03:28,175
I finally made
it to nationals,

56
00:03:28,175 --> 00:03:30,077
but the fact that I
have to play with him

57
00:03:30,077 --> 00:03:32,612
makes me wish we'd
never gotten this far.

58
00:03:32,612 --> 00:03:34,014
(sighing)

59
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:35,816
Hmm!

60
00:03:35,816 --> 00:03:41,555
♪

61
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:44,191
Hey, bro, how's it going?

62
00:03:44,191 --> 00:03:45,792
Oh, hey, I didn't
see you there.

63
00:03:45,792 --> 00:03:47,627
(chuckling)

64
00:03:47,627 --> 00:03:50,163
(grunting)

65
00:03:50,163 --> 00:03:52,065
‐Huh?
‐Hmm.

66
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:54,134
Well, it looks like
everyone's here.

67
00:03:54,134 --> 00:03:56,970
What do you say, guys,
should we hit the road?

68
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:58,105
I call shotgun.

69
00:03:58,105 --> 00:04:00,107
Uh, sorry, Kamui,
you can't sit up front.

70
00:04:00,107 --> 00:04:01,575
Misaki needs that spot.

71
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:02,909
What?

72
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:05,112
He won't be able to find the
way there without my help.

73
00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:08,248
If you don't know the roads,
just buy a GPS or a map,

74
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,350
you great for something.

75
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:11,318
I'm sorry, were you trying

76
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:12,452
to call me a
"good‐for‐nothing"?

77
00:04:12,452 --> 00:04:13,754
Yeah, that's the one.

78
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,255
Why should I buy a GPS

79
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,257
when Misaki can
memorize the directions?

80
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,426
I guess you got
a point there.

81
00:04:19,426 --> 00:04:21,094
Hmm, I win.

82
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:23,196
Eh, like I care.

83
00:04:23,196 --> 00:04:27,134
I'll just grab one of
the back window seats.

84
00:04:27,134 --> 00:04:29,903
Ugh, you're kidding me!

85
00:04:29,903 --> 00:04:31,705
What now?

86
00:04:31,705 --> 00:04:33,473
You're sitting in my seat!

87
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:35,709
‐Really?
‐Oh, so now you're gonna act

88
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,444
like you don't know
what I'm talking about.

89
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:40,480
Listen, Kai, I always
sit by the window.

90
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,815
Like I care.

91
00:04:41,815 --> 00:04:43,750
Ah!

92
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:44,885
It's okay.

93
00:04:44,885 --> 00:04:46,653
There's another window
seat on this side.

94
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:49,256
You can both have one.

95
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:53,059
(yawning)

96
00:04:53,059 --> 00:04:54,995
(chuckling)

97
00:04:56,429 --> 00:04:59,232
All right, team, here we go.

98
00:04:59,232 --> 00:05:05,472
♪

99
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:06,506
Take that right turn.

100
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:08,375
Sure thing.

101
00:05:09,876 --> 00:05:11,144
I said, "Right!"

102
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,345
Huh?

103
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:14,080
Ah!

104
00:05:15,682 --> 00:05:18,285
(meowing)

105
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:20,287
Some driver.

106
00:05:21,888 --> 00:05:23,523
(gulping)

107
00:05:23,523 --> 00:05:27,093
Oh, boy, that hits the spot.

108
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:29,095
(train horn blaring)

109
00:05:29,095 --> 00:05:39,606
♪

110
00:05:41,107 --> 00:05:43,343
‐Wow!
‐No way!

111
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:45,245
I'm pretty sure this
is the back entrance.

112
00:05:45,245 --> 00:05:46,313
Seriously?

113
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:48,615
The tournament hall for
the regional championships

114
00:05:48,615 --> 00:05:50,217
was impressive,
but it's nothing

115
00:05:50,217 --> 00:05:51,751
compared to this stadium.

116
00:05:51,751 --> 00:05:52,586
What do you expect?

117
00:05:52,586 --> 00:05:54,621
This is the
nationals, after all,

118
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:57,991
and I'd say it's probably
gonna be a sold‐out crowd.

119
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:58,959
Whoa.

120
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:00,627
I'm gonna go drive
around for a bit

121
00:06:00,627 --> 00:06:02,562
and try to find a place
to park this thing.

122
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:04,464
You guys hang tight
here till I get back.

123
00:06:04,464 --> 00:06:06,466
Sounds good.

124
00:06:07,901 --> 00:06:10,270
Ten bucks says he gets
lost and doesn't make it.

125
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:12,439
Guess we'll be
taking the train home.

126
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:14,241
No thanks.

127
00:06:14,241 --> 00:06:17,110
Huh?

128
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,578
What's that all about?

129
00:06:18,578 --> 00:06:20,480
Oh, that's just one
of the network crews

130
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,681
that'll be around
filming stuff

131
00:06:21,681 --> 00:06:24,084
for the live television
broadcast later today.

132
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:25,886
What, you're kidding?

133
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:28,955
They always show the
Vanguard Nationals on TV.

134
00:06:28,955 --> 00:06:30,490
Haven't you seen it before?

135
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,258
No.

136
00:06:31,258 --> 00:06:32,726
Hey, take a look, you guys!

137
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:35,595
I think that might be
Dr. O over there.

138
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:37,931
(indistinct chattering)

139
00:06:37,931 --> 00:06:40,500
Which means Vanguard
TV must be here!

140
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,135
Come on, bro, let's
go see if we can get

141
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:44,170
his autograph or something.

142
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,273
I've always wanted to
meet a famous person,

143
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:47,674
and here's my chance!

144
00:06:47,674 --> 00:06:50,510
All right, follow me!

145
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,579
Kamui!

146
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:54,180
I'm sorry, I didn't
see you there.

147
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,749
That looked bad.

148
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:56,750
Hmm?

149
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:59,219
♪

150
00:06:59,219 --> 00:07:01,388
"Ancient Roman History"?

151
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:03,123
Hey, are you
gonna be all right?

152
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:05,392
Don't worry, bro,
I'll be just fine.

153
00:07:05,392 --> 00:07:06,459
Oh, thank goodness.

154
00:07:06,459 --> 00:07:07,894
"Oh, thank goodness."

155
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:10,430
You're not getting off
that easy, you big oaf!

156
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,898
It feels like I
just got run over

157
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:13,767
by a dump truck
full of rocks.

158
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:15,769
You're right, it was
super careless of me

159
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:17,304
to get run into like
that all of a sudden.

160
00:07:17,304 --> 00:07:20,340
Please, accept my
most humble apology.

161
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:21,641
I'm sorry.

162
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:23,510
I shouldn't have
lost my temper.

163
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:25,812
Sorry for running into you
and blaming you for it.

164
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:27,580
He didn't mean to.

165
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:29,082
What's going on, Koutei?

166
00:07:29,082 --> 00:07:30,417
Are you getting us
into trouble?

167
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:33,820
It's okay, we just had a
little accident, that's all.

168
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,322
Are you okay, little guy?

169
00:07:35,322 --> 00:07:36,423
Did you get hurt anywhere?

170
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:37,457
Little guy?

171
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,226
Don't talk down to me
like I'm some kid.

172
00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:42,662
That sure is a nasty
scrape on your elbow.

173
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,331
Hold on a second,
I'm pretty sure I have

174
00:07:44,331 --> 00:07:45,932
a bandage with me.

175
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:48,435
It's no big deal, so just
give it a rest, all right?

176
00:07:48,435 --> 00:07:49,669
Oh, no, you're injured?

177
00:07:49,669 --> 00:07:51,304
I feel really bad about this.

178
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:52,672
Everything's fine.

179
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:54,107
Here.

180
00:07:54,107 --> 00:07:56,876
Oh, great, thank you.

181
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:57,978
Okay.

182
00:07:57,978 --> 00:07:59,746
Who's a big, brave boy?

183
00:07:59,746 --> 00:08:02,148
Yeah, well,
don't expect me to thank you.

184
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,683
You're welcome anyway.

185
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,051
(chuckling)

186
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:07,620
Just sad.

187
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,888
Huh?

188
00:08:08,888 --> 00:08:10,757
(grunting)

189
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:12,292
Just great, you
knocked me over,

190
00:08:12,292 --> 00:08:14,094
and now I don't
get to meet Dr. O!

191
00:08:14,094 --> 00:08:17,330
Oh, as if it wasn't
bad enough already.

192
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,398
I'm really sorry.

193
00:08:18,398 --> 00:08:20,200
Could he be any nicer?

194
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:27,007
Hmm, those kids.

195
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,274
What do you think
they're up to?

196
00:08:28,274 --> 00:08:30,210
Looks like they're
arguing with another team.

197
00:08:30,210 --> 00:08:31,578
I don't know how
long they'll last

198
00:08:31,578 --> 00:08:32,946
if they go around
picking fights.

199
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:34,180
I wonder.

200
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:36,683
Wait, I just realized
who they're talking to.

201
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:37,884
What are the chances?

202
00:08:37,884 --> 00:08:39,753
You're Team Caesar?

203
00:08:39,753 --> 00:08:41,621
So, you've heard
of them before?

204
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:43,323
Are you kidding me, bro?

205
00:08:43,323 --> 00:08:44,591
They were last
year's runner‐up,

206
00:08:44,591 --> 00:08:48,395
and the year before, they
were national champions!

207
00:08:48,395 --> 00:08:50,897
I had no idea.

208
00:08:50,897 --> 00:08:53,967
Hey, look, everyone.

209
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:55,568
It's Team Caesar.

210
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:58,238
Oh, so the former
champions have returned then.

211
00:08:58,238 --> 00:09:01,207
I bet they're looking
to get some revenge.

212
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:02,776
I think we should
go find a place

213
00:09:02,776 --> 00:09:05,145
that's a little less crowded.

214
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:08,348
I'd rather not have all
these eyes staring at me.

215
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:11,351
Huh.

216
00:09:11,351 --> 00:09:14,788
They must be really strong.

217
00:09:14,788 --> 00:09:16,956
Oh, no, our bags!

218
00:09:16,956 --> 00:09:19,192
Sorry, we just need a minute!

219
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:21,895
Amazing, it's like they were
meant to meet or something.

220
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,830
It's only a coincidence.

221
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:26,166
Was it fate or
just dumb luck?

222
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,767
We'll know the answer
to that question

223
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,602
once this tournament is over.

224
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:30,770
Right.

225
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,972
What do you mean?

226
00:09:32,972 --> 00:09:34,674
This spot's better.

227
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,143
Isn't it about time you
got over your stage fright?

228
00:09:37,143 --> 00:09:39,112
I just don't like it
when people look at me.

229
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:41,381
And, yet, when thousands of
fans are watching you play,

230
00:09:41,381 --> 00:09:42,382
you're totally fine.

231
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:45,118
What a strange guy.

232
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:46,586
I don't think
we had the chance

233
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,721
to properly
introduce ourselves.

234
00:09:48,721 --> 00:09:50,457
The name's Kenji Mitsusada,

235
00:09:50,457 --> 00:09:52,158
and I'm the leader
of Team Caesar.

236
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,726
Just call me Yuri.

237
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:54,928
She's my big sister.

238
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:55,962
They call me Gai.

239
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:58,164
Wait, so your name's
Kenji Mitsusada?

240
00:09:58,164 --> 00:10:00,800
I thought you called him
by a different name earlier.

241
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,535
Oh, yeah, Koutei.

242
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:04,270
‐Koutei?
‐Yeah.

243
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,606
It's a nickname he
got when we were kids.

244
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,209
So I guess you've been
friends for a long time.

245
00:10:09,209 --> 00:10:10,310
So what's the reason for you

246
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:11,911
calling yourselves
"Team Caesar"?

247
00:10:11,911 --> 00:10:13,113
Yeah, good question.

248
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:14,447
I guess I should explain,

249
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:15,682
otherwise you'll
wind up thinking

250
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:17,884
we're named after a
salad or something.

251
00:10:17,884 --> 00:10:19,752
See, nearly 2,000 years ago,

252
00:10:19,752 --> 00:10:22,555
this guy named Julius Caesar
lived in Ancient Rome

253
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,624
and he was a
powerful general who‐‐

254
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:26,659
Spare us the lecture.

255
00:10:26,659 --> 00:10:28,561
But I was about to
get to the good part.

256
00:10:28,561 --> 00:10:30,697
Yeah, well, I don't
want to hear any parts,

257
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:32,198
good, bad, or otherwise.

258
00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:35,935
Fine, how about we settle for
the story of Octavius then?

259
00:10:35,935 --> 00:10:37,137
Kidding.

260
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:39,806
Basically, Koutei is a huge
fan of Ancient Roman history,

261
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:41,241
so we named ourselves after

262
00:10:41,241 --> 00:10:42,675
one of their
greatest emperors.

263
00:10:42,675 --> 00:10:43,510
That makes sense, right?

264
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:44,611
Sure does.

265
00:10:44,611 --> 00:10:46,846
(screaming)

266
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:49,816
It's my Kourin!

267
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,918
Morikawa's here?

268
00:10:51,918 --> 00:10:53,219
(chuckling)

269
00:10:53,219 --> 00:10:55,021
Finally, my collection
of Ultra Rare

270
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:57,123
limited‐edition
merchandise is complete!

271
00:10:57,123 --> 00:10:59,893
I've just accomplished
all I set out to do today.

272
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:01,161
So that was your whole reason

273
00:11:01,161 --> 00:11:02,729
for coming to the
national tournament?

274
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:06,833
I guess cheering for Team Q4
will have to take a back seat.

275
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,501
Don't look too
jealous there, guys.

276
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:10,737
This little baby just
gave me a huge boost

277
00:11:10,737 --> 00:11:12,372
to my Ultra Rare
fan club points,

278
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:14,807
which pretty much means
I'm the best boyfriend ever,

279
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:17,043
if I'm not mistaken.

280
00:11:17,043 --> 00:11:20,980
Hey, Aichi, look at all
the cool stuff I got!

281
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:22,248
Give it a rest, man.

282
00:11:22,248 --> 00:11:23,516
Try and stop me!

283
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,618
Annoying as he is,
there's something reflexing

284
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:26,853
about seeing him here,

285
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:28,454
‐you know?
‐Relaxing?

286
00:11:28,454 --> 00:11:29,722
Having some friendly faces

287
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:31,357
around really
puts you at ease.

288
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:32,592
Hardly.

289
00:11:32,592 --> 00:11:35,762
That reminds me, weren't Reiji
and Eiji gonna come today?

290
00:11:35,762 --> 00:11:40,133
Oh, no, I hope those two
didn't take the wrong train.

291
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:42,402
Actually, if Morikawa
managed to make it,

292
00:11:42,402 --> 00:11:44,604
I'm sure they won't have any
problems finding their way.

293
00:11:44,604 --> 00:11:45,772
Good call.

294
00:11:45,772 --> 00:11:47,507
Watch what you say
about me, Kamui,

295
00:11:47,507 --> 00:11:49,042
or I'll have to
come over there!

296
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,044
Could he actually hear me?

297
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,880
Nah, he probably just
assumed you said it.

298
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,181
Impressive.

299
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:56,416
Totally.

300
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:59,719
Hmm, weird, I feel like
we're forgetting something.

301
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:01,654
Where is everyone?

302
00:12:01,654 --> 00:12:04,357
I told you to wait
here and you didn't.

303
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:08,294
♪

304
00:12:11,864 --> 00:12:17,136
♪

305
00:12:17,136 --> 00:12:19,272
(cheering)

306
00:12:19,272 --> 00:12:29,816
♪

307
00:12:29,816 --> 00:12:32,619
♪ Nothing could
be stopping me ♪

308
00:12:32,619 --> 00:12:35,788
♪ I don't care,
whatever, you see ♪

309
00:12:35,788 --> 00:12:38,291
♪ (indistinct lyrics) ♪

310
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:41,494
♪ Don't tell me what to do ♪

311
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:44,597
♪ If you live in
this magic moment ♪

312
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,366
♪ Open your arms

313
00:12:46,366 --> 00:12:51,271
and sing, the moment
will just be worthwhile ♪

314
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:54,540
♪ Look in the eyes
on their lives ♪

315
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:57,176
♪ Having no sparkle, why ♪

316
00:12:57,176 --> 00:12:58,778
♪ And I swear ♪

317
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:03,182
♪ I'm just me, ain't
gonna be anyone else ♪

318
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:05,985
♪ But if inside my heart ♪

319
00:13:05,985 --> 00:13:08,621
♪ How this fire
makes you smile ♪

320
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:11,424
I love you!

321
00:13:11,424 --> 00:13:14,127
Cheer louder, guys,
and put on that robe!

322
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:16,296
‐Me too?
‐Obviously.

323
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:18,898
This is the whole
reason we came, right?

324
00:13:18,898 --> 00:13:20,667
‐As if!
‐As if!

325
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:22,302
Wow, they're putting
a lot more effort

326
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:24,570
into the opening
ceremonies this year.

327
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:26,372
You mean it's not
always like this?

328
00:13:26,372 --> 00:13:28,041
Well, they do their best
to make it exciting,

329
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:29,876
but this is taking it
to a whole new level.

330
00:13:29,876 --> 00:13:31,444
‐I mean...
‐Kourin!

331
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:33,680
...a concert by Ultra
Rare is pretty big.

332
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,715
If they plan on doing
the same thing next year,

333
00:13:35,715 --> 00:13:37,817
I'll be sure to bring
some ear plugs.

334
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,452
This might not be
our type of music,

335
00:13:39,452 --> 00:13:40,920
but it looks like
those guys are having

336
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,188
the time of their lives.

337
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:44,590
Uh, did she just call me
one of these guys?

338
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:49,128
The men of Earth can't
get enough of Ultra Rare!

339
00:13:49,128 --> 00:13:51,964
Nonsense.

340
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:54,701
Which one of you called
my Ultra Rare "nonsense"?

341
00:13:54,701 --> 00:13:55,902
Calm down, Morikawa.

342
00:13:55,902 --> 00:13:58,571
I didn't hear anyone over
there say that sort of thing.

343
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:00,506
Really, 'cause I
could have sworn

344
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:04,944
I heard someone
say that, or did I?

345
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:06,012
He acts without thinking,

346
00:14:06,012 --> 00:14:08,514
and then immediately
doubts himself.

347
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:10,983
This guy's ridiculous.

348
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:13,553
Hey, what's it like being
on a team with four players?

349
00:14:13,553 --> 00:14:15,521
Do your top three players
hog all the action,

350
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:16,956
or does everyone
get a chance?

351
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:18,358
Huh?

352
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:19,459
Do you change up your order

353
00:14:19,459 --> 00:14:22,261
based on who your
opponent is or...

354
00:14:22,261 --> 00:14:25,832
Or maybe you guys don't
waste time thinking about it.

355
00:14:25,832 --> 00:14:28,167
Well, we, uh...

356
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:29,235
I forgot.

357
00:14:29,235 --> 00:14:31,237
We'll be fighting as
a three‐person team

358
00:14:31,237 --> 00:14:34,574
just like at the
regional tournament.

359
00:14:34,574 --> 00:14:37,243
Misaki wasn't there
last time, so she's in.

360
00:14:37,243 --> 00:14:40,613
Between Kai and Kamui, I don't
think I can steal a spot.

361
00:14:40,613 --> 00:14:42,248
Guess I'm sitting out.

362
00:14:42,248 --> 00:14:43,716
Give it a rest, Gai.

363
00:14:43,716 --> 00:14:46,719
It's rude to poke your nose
into another team's strategy.

364
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:47,687
Oh.

365
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:48,921
It doesn't matter.

366
00:14:48,921 --> 00:14:51,624
‐Huh?
‐Hmm?

367
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:55,261
Deciding who plays doesn't
involve any strategy.

368
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:57,797
It's easy, the weakest
player on our team

369
00:14:57,797 --> 00:14:59,932
will always sit out.

370
00:14:59,932 --> 00:15:01,033
And that's final.

371
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:02,702
‐Oh, yeah?
‐Problem?

372
00:15:02,702 --> 00:15:05,471
How about you show some
respect to your teammates?

373
00:15:05,471 --> 00:15:06,539
Hmm.

374
00:15:06,539 --> 00:15:08,908
Calm down, guys, there's
no need to get angry.

375
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:10,910
Look, this is
Team Q4 business,

376
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:13,312
and I'd appreciate it if
you kept out, all right?

377
00:15:13,312 --> 00:15:14,414
Uh, sure.

378
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:18,151
I don't care about
you or this team.

379
00:15:18,151 --> 00:15:20,620
‐That's it.
‐It's okay, Kamui.

380
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:22,422
‐Come on, bro.
‐I know I'm not gonna get

381
00:15:22,422 --> 00:15:25,691
the chance to play.

382
00:15:25,691 --> 00:15:28,127
Kai's right, we should
have our top three players

383
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:30,730
representing the team
whenever possible.

384
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:32,165
And with the way
you guys play,

385
00:15:32,165 --> 00:15:34,634
we all know who
the weakest link is.

386
00:15:34,634 --> 00:15:36,969
I don't mind.

387
00:15:36,969 --> 00:15:39,372
Are you sure?

388
00:15:39,372 --> 00:15:40,840
That settles it then.

389
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,543
(grunting)

390
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:47,447
There's something
I need to know, Kai.

391
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:50,883
Why does a guy like you
even play Vanguard anyway?

392
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:54,520
The thrill of taking a strong
player and destroying them.

393
00:15:55,755 --> 00:15:59,225
That's the whole reason
I play this game.

394
00:15:59,225 --> 00:16:01,994
Is that all?

395
00:16:01,994 --> 00:16:04,230
Yeah.

396
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:06,833
Well then.

397
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:10,069
♪

398
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:13,072
You know, the whole reason I
started going to Card Capital

399
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:16,542
is that there wasn't
anywhere else for me to play.

400
00:16:16,542 --> 00:16:18,344
I needed to get
myself as far away

401
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:20,146
from Team Handsome as possible,

402
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:23,449
so I decided to try card
fighting at a different store.

403
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:25,184
I was only in it for myself.

404
00:16:25,184 --> 00:16:27,153
I didn't care about the
team or the rest of you,

405
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:30,957
as long as we won our games.

406
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:32,325
But all that's changed now

407
00:16:32,325 --> 00:16:34,427
'cause I know we have
something special.

408
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:38,564
I want us to win this
tournament together.

409
00:16:38,564 --> 00:16:40,333
I don't get you.

410
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,102
You don't care about anybody.

411
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:46,239
If she wants to quit,
I say we let her do it.

412
00:16:46,239 --> 00:16:47,306
But, Kai...

413
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:49,609
You act like she's the
only one with a past.

414
00:16:49,609 --> 00:16:51,978
If she's gonna use a car
accident as an excuse

415
00:16:51,978 --> 00:16:55,014
for her own weakness,
then we don't need her.

416
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,582
How can you act so heartless

417
00:16:56,582 --> 00:16:58,551
to the people
around you, Kai?

418
00:16:58,551 --> 00:17:00,586
(sighing)

419
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,356
I guess being on this team

420
00:17:03,356 --> 00:17:06,292
doesn't mean anything
to you, does it?

421
00:17:06,292 --> 00:17:07,960
Forget the team.

422
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,997
When I'm card fighting,
none of you matter to me.

423
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:12,865
That's it.

424
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:15,501
Kamui.

425
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:17,904
That's the last draw.

426
00:17:17,904 --> 00:17:19,005
Straw?

427
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:21,641
Bro, I hate to do this to ya,

428
00:17:21,641 --> 00:17:23,609
but there's just no way
I can bring myself

429
00:17:23,609 --> 00:17:26,412
to fight alongside a
jerk like him anymore.

430
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:27,880
Sorry.

431
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:31,450
‐I quit!
‐No, Kamui, wait!

432
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,852
Huh?

433
00:17:32,852 --> 00:17:34,720
‐What's going on?
‐Beats me.

434
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:35,755
Oh!

435
00:17:35,755 --> 00:17:36,756
Oh, good!

436
00:17:36,756 --> 00:17:38,558
I've been looking
all over the place.

437
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:40,860
It took me
forever to find you.

438
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,461
I'm sorry, I can't
stay and talk.

439
00:17:42,461 --> 00:17:43,796
I'm in a hurry right now.

440
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:46,465
Oh, you gotta use the
bathroom or something?

441
00:17:46,465 --> 00:17:48,834
Hold on, you can't leave.

442
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:50,336
Now that the concert's over,

443
00:17:50,336 --> 00:17:51,904
it's time for all
the teams to head out

444
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,005
onto the tournament floor

445
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:55,141
and draw the pairings
for the first round.

446
00:17:55,141 --> 00:17:57,276
Wow, we're starting already?

447
00:17:57,276 --> 00:17:59,679
(grunting)

448
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:01,847
Let's not waste any time.

449
00:18:01,847 --> 00:18:03,883
♪

450
00:18:03,883 --> 00:18:06,118
Come on, Aichi.

451
00:18:06,118 --> 00:18:07,820
Hmm, you mean...

452
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:09,155
Now that Kamui's
out of the picture,

453
00:18:09,155 --> 00:18:11,657
we're down to three members,
so if you don't come with us,

454
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:14,026
then Team Q4 is
gonna have to forfeit.

455
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:15,127
Is that what you want?

456
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:17,697
Wait, Kamui quit the team?

457
00:18:17,697 --> 00:18:19,065
What happened
while I was gone?

458
00:18:19,065 --> 00:18:20,933
‐I don't know.
‐Not sure.

459
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,469
No clue.

460
00:18:23,469 --> 00:18:25,671
Want my advice?

461
00:18:25,671 --> 00:18:27,840
Koutei?

462
00:18:29,542 --> 00:18:31,811
You know that is just the
first day of the tournament

463
00:18:31,811 --> 00:18:34,213
and the big games don't
happen until next week, right?

464
00:18:34,213 --> 00:18:36,015
‐Uh, yeah?
‐Well, the games

465
00:18:36,015 --> 00:18:38,150
you're about to play
are elimination matches,

466
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:39,318
and if your team loses,

467
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:41,621
you won't be able to
compete in the finals.

468
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:45,224
You just need to see how
much is on the line here.

469
00:18:45,224 --> 00:18:48,127
♪

470
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:50,363
I know you want to chase
after your friend right now,

471
00:18:50,363 --> 00:18:51,731
but if you don't play today,

472
00:18:51,731 --> 00:18:54,100
there won't be a team
for him to come back to.

473
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:57,103
Sometimes doing what's
right isn't easy.

474
00:18:57,103 --> 00:18:58,971
I guess so.

475
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,906
Good choice,
'cause that's what

476
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:03,042
being on a team is all about.

477
00:19:03,042 --> 00:19:05,177
Yeah, totally.

478
00:19:05,177 --> 00:19:07,413
(sighing)

479
00:19:07,413 --> 00:19:09,715
Oh, no, I think this
is the rear entrance.

480
00:19:09,715 --> 00:19:11,550
Oh, man, I thought you said

481
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:13,185
this was gonna be
a shortcut, yo.

482
00:19:13,185 --> 00:19:14,920
(panting)

483
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:17,623
We're so late, I bet the
tournament's already started.

484
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:19,959
Not to worry, I checked
the schedule online,

485
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:22,028
and it looks like we're
gonna be just in time.

486
00:19:22,028 --> 00:19:25,231
Huh, hey, that's Kamui.

487
00:19:25,231 --> 00:19:26,866
Wait for us!

488
00:19:26,866 --> 00:19:29,568
Can you show us where
the entrance is, yo?

489
00:19:31,504 --> 00:19:32,972
I'm exhausted.

490
00:19:32,972 --> 00:19:36,008
Really, you don't get
excited singing for everyone?

491
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:39,211
I just don't have the energy
for this kind of thing.

492
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:40,713
Oh, it's 'cause
you're old, right?

493
00:19:40,713 --> 00:19:42,581
That's enough.

494
00:19:42,581 --> 00:19:44,717
Just for that, I'm gonna
sing all your lines

495
00:19:44,717 --> 00:19:46,018
in our next
performance, Rekka.

496
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,553
No, but that's not fair!

497
00:19:47,553 --> 00:19:49,689
What's this?

498
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:50,956
Suiko?

499
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:52,358
Oh.

500
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:54,593
He's from that team.

501
00:19:54,593 --> 00:19:55,728
You think they...

502
00:19:55,728 --> 00:19:56,896
...had a fight?

503
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:58,431
(knocking)

504
00:19:58,431 --> 00:20:01,100
We need you back on stage in
a couple of minutes, ladies.

505
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,201
Please be ready.

506
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:04,737
‐Sounds good.
‐Let's go!

507
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,608
And, now, allow me
to introduce you

508
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:12,845
to the master of ceremonies
you all know and love.

509
00:20:12,845 --> 00:20:14,747
It's me, of course, MC Mya!

510
00:20:14,747 --> 00:20:17,149
Nobody likes you,
so get off the stage,

511
00:20:17,149 --> 00:20:19,552
you lousy waste of space!

512
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:21,420
Listen up, four eyes!

513
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:23,122
We don't need to hear
you blathering on

514
00:20:23,122 --> 00:20:25,591
with your phony excitement,
so why don't do your job

515
00:20:25,591 --> 00:20:28,761
and just get Ultra Rare
back on the stage?

516
00:20:28,761 --> 00:20:30,596
There's always a critic.

517
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:33,299
Hurry up, and get
Kourin back on the stage!

518
00:20:33,299 --> 00:20:34,233
Really?

519
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,202
And stop holding
the mic like that!

520
00:20:36,202 --> 00:20:38,404
Not you, too.

521
00:20:38,404 --> 00:20:40,372
These guys.

522
00:20:40,372 --> 00:20:42,508
Without further ado,
it's time we said hello

523
00:20:42,508 --> 00:20:44,276
to my lovely
co‐host for the day.

524
00:20:44,276 --> 00:20:46,645
It's Rekka, Suiko, and Kourin.

525
00:20:46,645 --> 00:20:49,348
Here they are,
folks, Ultra Rare!

526
00:20:49,348 --> 00:20:51,350
(cheering)

527
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:56,956
♪

528
00:20:56,956 --> 00:20:59,725
I've waited so long
for this moment, Kourin.

529
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:00,993
Yeah, how long?

530
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:02,895
Dude, it's only been
about ten minutes.

531
00:21:02,895 --> 00:21:04,864
But those ten
minutes apart from her

532
00:21:04,864 --> 00:21:07,366
were like ten long years
on a desert island.

533
00:21:07,366 --> 00:21:08,834
‐Yeah, yeah.
‐Yeah, yeah.

534
00:21:08,834 --> 00:21:11,604
What a great day for a
Vanguard Tournament, right?

535
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:12,905
Right!

536
00:21:12,905 --> 00:21:15,875
Okay, everyone on this side,
make some noise for me.

537
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:18,110
(cheering)

